<dl id="n42050e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42050e">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42050e"> 50(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> benchers = / beggars</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">outside the prophet&apos;s house was a bench or gallery on which were always to be found <mark>a number of poor</mark>, who lived entirely upon his generosity, and were hence called &lsquo;<mark>the people of the bench</mark>.&rsquo; <small> Stanley Lane-Poole, <a name="SLPS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SLPS"><cite title="source">The Speeches and Table-Talk of the Prophet Mohammad</cite></a> (1882) xxx</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
